ent-RMCGunRackType71EmptyPVE-name = Type 71 gun rack
ent-RMCGunRackType71EmptyPVE-desc = Some off-branded gun rack. Per SOF and SPPA regulations, weapons should be stored in secure safes and only given out when necessary. Of course, most (but not all!) units overlook this regulation, only storing their firearms in safes when inspection arrives.

ent-RMCGunRackType71Empty-name = Type 71 gun rack
ent-RMCGunRackType71Empty-desc = Some off-branded gun rack. Per SOF and SPPA regulations, weapons should be stored in secure safes and only given out when necessary. Of course, most (but not all!) units overlook this regulation, only storing their firearms in safes when inspection arrives.

ent-RMCGunRackSSG45Empty-name = SSG45 gun rack
ent-RMCGunRackSSG45Empty-desc = AEGIS-produced gun rack for storage of long guns. While initial model was supposed to be extremely modifiable, Weston-Yamada commissioned racks with fixed slots which only fit SSG45 rifles. Some say they were cheaper, and some say the main reason was operators' ability to easily break anything more complex than a tungsten ball.

